## Unit 4b: vector<T> and deque<T>

### Basic Operations

- **`std::vector`**: Dynamic array that can resize.
- **`std::deque`**: Double-ended queue that allows fast insertions/removals at both ends.

### Efficiency of Their Operations

- **`vector<T>`**:
  - Access: O(1)
  - Insertion at end: Amortized O(1)
  - Insertion/removal at beginning or middle: O(n)

- **`deque<T>`**:
  - Access: O(1)
  - Insertion/removal at both ends: O(1)

