## Unit 4d: Multidimensional Arrays

### Memory Layout

Multidimensional arrays are stored in contiguous memory locations in row-major or column-major order.

### Passing Multidimensional Arrays to Functions

**Syntax**:
```cpp
void processArray(int arr[][COLS], int rows);
```

**Example**:
```cpp
void printMatrix(int arr[3][3]) {
    for (int i = 0; i < 3; ++i) {
        for (int j = 0; j < 3; ++j) {
            std::cout << arr[i][j] << " ";
        }
        std::cout << std::endl;
    }
}
```

